<paragraph blockId="134.[151,1437,1124,1223]" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">
Small rare gomphids (
<figureCitation box="[402,487,1161,1187]" captionStart="FIGURE 74" captionStartId="134.[151,250,1947,1972]" captionTargetBox="[340,1243,1269,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@134.[340,1247,1245,1928]" captionTargetPageId="134" captionText="FIGURE 74. Perigomphus angularis holotype ♂: ECUADOR, Morona-Santiago Province, Huamboya Canton: small stream 1 km S of Río Pasanac, Hwy. 45, 16 x 2005, leg. K. Tennessen; photo K. Schnepp." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335777/files/figure.png" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Fig. 74</figureCitation>
), with one of the three known species recorded so far in 
<collectingCountry box="[1130,1223,1161,1187]" name="Ecuador" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tennessen, K. J." box="[1239,1425,1161,1187]" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" pagination="66 - 68" refId="ref203475" refString="Tennessen, K. J. (2011) Perigomphus angularis spec. nov. from central Ecuador (Odonata: Gomphidae). Zootaxa, 2915 (1), 66 - 68. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2915.1.7" type="journal article" year="2011">Tennessen 2011</bibRefCitation>
). Habitat is small, shallow forest streams.
</paragraph>
